<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<knowl mode="exercise" xmlns="https://spatext.clontz.org" version="0.2">
    <knowl>
        <content>
            <p>Manipulate each expression below until they have the form 
            <m>r \ln( {{p}} )</m> for some rational number <m>r</m>.</p>
            <list>
            <item><p><m> \ln\left( {{arg11}} \right) 
                    + \ln\left( {{arg21}} \right) </m></p></item>
            <item><p><m> \ln\left( {{arg12}} \sqrt{ {{g}} } \right) 
                - \ln\left( {{arg22}}  \sqrt{ {{g}} } \right) </m></p></item>
            </list>
        </content>
        <outtro>
            <list>
            <item><p>The given expression equals <m> {{disp_r1}} \ln( {{p}} )</m>. 
            In other words, <m>r = {{r1}}</m>.</p></item>
            <item><p>The given expression equals <m> {{disp_r2}} \ln( {{p}} )</m>. 
            In other words, <m>r = {{r2}}</m>.</p></item>
            </list>
        </outtro>
    </knowl>
    <knowl>
        <content>
            <p>Manipulate the expression 
                <m mode = "display">
                    \ln\left[ {{f}} \right]
                </m>
                into a sum/difference of terms of the form <m>r \ln(f(x))</m> where
                each <m>r</m> is an integer, and each <m>f(x)</m> is an irreducible 
                algebraic expression.
            </p>
        </content>
        <outtro>
            <p><m mode="display">
                {{pp}} \ln(x)
                + {{qq}} \ln( {{afact}} )
                + {{rr}} \ln( {{bfact}} )
                - \ln( {{c1fact}} )
                - \ln( {{c2fact}} )
            </m></p>
        </outtro>
    </knowl>
</knowl>
